OL,3,CFishermen recall mystery of 'yellow
OL,4,Csubmarine' hauled ashore on Islay in
OL,5,C2005
OL,7,FDespite Royal Navy markings on the
OL,8,Fside of the yellow submersible, the
OL,9,FMinistry of Defence initially denied
OL,10,Fit owned it.
OL,12,FThe submarine then found its way into
OL,13,Fthe garden of Harold Hastie ` Mr
OL,14,FBaker's brother-in-law ` in Port
OL,15,FEllen, where it became a local tourist
OL,16,Fattraction.
OL,18,FThe mystery around the ownership of
OL,19,Fthe "yellow submarine" prompted
OL,20,Finternational media attention.
OL,26,@{D@EOU{D@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1780275788
OL,3,CFishermen recall mystery of 'yellow
OL,4,Csubmarine' hauled ashore on Islay in
OL,5,C2005
OL,7,FIt was only in September 2005 that the
OL,8,FRoyal Navy dispatched minesweeper HMS
OL,9,FBlyth to retrieve the craft, after
OL,10,Feventually admitting it was its
OL,11,Fproperty.
OL,13,FThe "yellow submarine" was in fact a
OL,14,Fremotely-operated vehicle used in mine-
OL,15,Fclearing operations.
OL,17,FBruichladdich distillery, which is
OL,18,Fbased on Islay, is releasing a special
OL,19,Fversion of its Yellow Submarine whisky
OL,20,Fthis year.
OL,26,@uD@EOUuD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
